page.title: 12THE RAILWAY STATION
page.content: When was it built? It was built in 1850 How many people work at the railway? Three What sort of trains go through the station? Freight trains,passenger trains and goods trains. How many trains go through the station now. 100 a day. How long have you had pay trains? Since 1967. Why does Elmswell need a station? For transport and to take the produce from the farms. Why have all the buildings gone? Because if you knock them down when you don't need them you pay less in rates. Thank you,what is your name? Mr.Creasy,......Goodbye.
